.\" Manpage for SimpleShell
.TH SIMPLESHELL 1 "August 2025" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
SimpleShell \- a minimal shell to execute commands and display environment variables
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simpleshell
[\fICOMMAND\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
SimpleShell is a lightweight command-line shell designed to execute programs available in the system \fPATH\fR or by absolute path.  
It also provides two built-in commands: \fBexit\fR and \fBenv\fR.  
.PP
This shell is intended for simple usage and educational purposes. Advanced shell features like pipes, redirection, background jobs, and scripting are not supported.
.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.
.TP
.B env
Displays the current environment variables.
.SH EXTERNAL COMMANDS
Any executable located in the system \fPATH\fR or specified by absolute path can be run with arguments.  
.PP
Example:
.RS
($) ls -l
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
This shell does not support traditional command-line options. Commands are entered interactively at the prompt.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Start the shell:
.RS
$ ./simpleshell
($) 
.RE
Run a command:
.RS
($) whoami
.RE
Display environment variables:
.RS
($) env
.RE
Exit the shell:
.RS
($) exit
.RE
.SH LIMITATIONS
.PP
- No support for pipes (\fB|\fR) or I/O redirection (\fB>\fR, \fB<\fR)  
- No background execution (\fB&\fR)  
- Only one command per line  
- No shell scripting support or expansions
.SH BUGS
No known bugs. Designed for educational and minimal usage.
.SH SEE ALSO
bash(1), sh(1)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Adel Mejrissi.

